Presentation Steps¶

  • [DATA_POOL]download and save klines of s&p 100 components
  • [FEATURE_POOL]generate features using data in data_pool(here just klines)
  • [MODEL_POOL]form a simple momentum model using features in feature_pool
  • [BACKTEST&ANALYSIS]using pyfolio to get a quick look for now

DATA_POOL¶

  • download adjusted kline data from yfinance from 20200101 to 20210701
  • 1 symbol (RTN) has no data because of delisted, for simplicity , I will use rest of 99 stocks to proceed

Backtest and Analysis using pyfolio¶

  • assume the one-side trading cost is 0.2%, and all the figures are shown based on this assumption.
  • use all cmp mean return as benchmark
  • if no cost is counted, the annual return would be 0.5%(almost 0)
In [8]:
trade_return=pd.read_pickle('../CLSA_test/FeaturePool/o2oret_1day.pkl').shift(-2) # the hold return if trade at today open and sell at tmr open
strat_daily_return=(trade_return*wgt).sum(axis=1)-wgt.diff().abs().sum(axis=1)*0.002
benchmarkt_daily_return=trade_return.mean(axis=1).to_frame('benchmark').benchmark
In [9]:
pf.create_full_tear_sheet(returns=strat_daily_return,positions=wgt.assign(cash=0),benchmark_rets=benchmarkt_daily_return)
